By whiskering, we define the natural transformations
  \theta  = F\xrightarrow {F\eta '}FGF'\xrightarrow {\epsilon  F'} F'\quad \text {and}\quad  \theta '   = F'\xrightarrow {F'\eta }F'GF\xrightarrow {\epsilon  F} F. Now the following diagram commutes:





