 commutes, which is immediate from the left triangle identity for F\dashv  G.
  In particular, the right arrow is (\epsilon ' F_*)_H = \epsilon '_{F_*H} =   \epsilon '_{FH} = \epsilon  FH. The right triangle identity and the case for
  pre-composition are similar, but in the latter case it is important to
  remember that pre-composition is contravariant, so that for
  instance in components the type of \eta '_H is H\to  FGH, not GFH.

