 be an adjunction with unit
1_C\xrightarrow {\eta } GF and counit FG\xrightarrow {\epsilon } 1_D. Then the
transpose f^\flat  of a map Fc\xrightarrow {f} d is given by the formula
f^\flat  = c\xrightarrow {\eta _c} GFc \xrightarrow {Gf} Gd. The transpose g^\sharp  of a map
c\xrightarrow {g} Gd is given by the formula g^\sharp  = Fc\xrightarrow {Fg} FGd \xrightarrow {\epsilon _d} d.

Fix a map Fc\xrightarrow {f} d. By naturality of the
  isomorphism D(Fc, d)\cong  C(c, Gd), the following square
  commutes:




